  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n                        \u003cp\u003eThe renovation of \u003ca href=\"https://pelletierdefontenay.com/Residence-Sutton-FR\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSutton House\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e in Sutton, Québec by \u003ca href=\"https://pelletierdefontenay.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePelletier de Fontenay\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e does not just preserve history – it transmutes it through its use of white cementitious coating, turning what was once a disparate collection of additions into a unified sculptural presence in the landscape. Rather than following the conventional preservation playbook of emphasizing material contrasts between old and new, the architects developed custom white mineral finishes that unify the building’s multiple iterations while allowing the underlying textures to remain legible. This approach creates a palimpsest effect – where, like an ancient manuscript that has been written over, the original text still shows through.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=570291\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-570291\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-12-810x540.jpg\" alt=\"Modern living space with a glass wall overlooking a garden, featuring a round table, chairs, a small plant, and a kitchen island. Large windows and a skylight provide natural light.\" width=\"810\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-12-810x540.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-12-800x534.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-12-768x512.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-12.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe decision to use hemp insulation – a bio-sourced material known for its breathability and humidity control – represents a marriage of traditional building techniques with contemporary environmental consciousness. This approach extends to the interior, where a sconce made of repurposed timber from the original structure serves as both functional lighting and a testament to the building’s history. The addition’s deep walls and thick roof echo the primitive heaviness of the original structure, while three distinct blocks frame views of the landscape.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=570295\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-570295\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-10-810x1208.jpg\" alt=\"Minimalist dining area with a wooden table and benches, a white pendant light, light wood floors, and a large window showing greenery.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1208\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-10-810x1208.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-10-800x1193.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-10-768x1145.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-10-1030x1536.jpg 1030w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-10.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe house employs passive strategies that would have been familiar to the original builders – thermal mass, natural ventilation, solar orientation – but updates them with contemporary technology. The limestone flooring sourced from local quarries serves dual purposes – it connects the building to its regional context while acting as thermal mass for passive solar heating.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=570289\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-570289\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-13-810x1149.jpg\" alt=\"Minimalist dining area with a round blue table, three wooden chairs, and a hanging lamp. Large window reveals a garden view with trees and grass. Neutral color palette.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1149\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-13-810x1149.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-13-800x1134.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-13-768x1089.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-13-1083x1536.jpg 1083w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-13.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=570293\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-570293\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-11-810x563.jpg\" alt=\"Minimalist interior with wooden floors, neutral walls, and large windows. A staircase on the left and a table with chairs visible in the distance. Bright, natural light fills the space.\" width=\"810\" height=\"563\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-11-810x563.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-11-800x556.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/02/suttonhouse-pelletierdefontenay-11-768x534.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/i